      • acceptsCategory

        boolean acceptsCategory(CategoryDefinition category)
        Checks whether methods from the given category shall be parsed or not

        category - The category in which the source or sink is defined

      • filter

        soot.jimple.infoflow.sourcesSinks.definitions.SourceSinkType filter(CategoryDefinition category,
                                                                    soot.jimple.infoflow.sourcesSinks.definitions.SourceSinkType sourceSinkType)
        Filters sources and sinks by category
        Parameters:
        category - The category in which the source or sink is defined
        sourceSinkType - Specifies whether the category is used for sources or sinks
        Returns:
        The acceptable use of the given category. This is a reduction from the given type. If the requested type, for example, is "Both", this method may return "Source", if the category shall only be used for sources, but not for sinks.
